'''James Cranna''' (c. [[1940s#1944|1944]] &mdash; [[May 4]], [[2017]])<ref name="SFGATE" /> was an actor who voiced the [[Ewok/Legends|Ewok]] [[Widdle Warrick/Legends|Widdle Warrick]] in ''[[Caravan of Courage: An Ewok Adventure]]'', and voiced the Ewok [[Teebo/Legends|Teebo]] in the [[Ewoks: Season Two|second season]] of the [[Ewoks (television series)|''Ewoks'']] animated television series. He was the only actor who participated in both of these related projects.

He also worked with [[George Lucas]] on the [[1971]] film ''THX 1138'' (in which he is credited as "Announcer"), the [[1973]] film [[Wikipedia:American Graffiti|''American Graffiti'']] (in which he is credited as "Liquor Store Thief"), the [[1983]] animated film [[Wikipedia:Twice Upon a Time|''Twice Upon a Time'']] (in which he voiced the characters of Rod Rescueman, Scuzzbopper, and Frivoli Foreman), and the [[1988]] film [[Wikipedia:Tucker: The Man and His Dream|''Tucker: The Man and His Dream'']] (in which he is credited as "Man in Audience").

